# Review routing for proofhouse-python-tool. GitHub applies the last
# matching rule, so the supply-chain rules below override the default
# for the paths they name. Owners are org teams (sole member @tbhb for
# now) created with push access, the minimum GitHub requires for a team
# to count as a code owner.

# Default owner for everything.
*                @proofhouse/maintainers

# Supply-chain and CI surface. The /.github/ rule already covers
# renovate.json5 and every workflow, so neither needs its own line.
/.github/        @proofhouse/security
/pyproject.toml  @proofhouse/security
/uv.lock         @proofhouse/security

# Release-pipeline ownership (@proofhouse/release-engineering) lands
# with the release workflow and its publishing config. Those files do
# not exist yet, so a rule here would point at nothing and fail the
# path-existence gate; it arrives alongside the release pipeline.
